<subSubSection id="AA562B6F120E1A3A08E5B932C27F8709" pageId="6" pageNumber="115" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3642CC50B8580ADC8725B41E36AA7395" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4EFD471916BBC5BAB394374F04AE1F14" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">
Large, 4.5 mm long (
<emphasis id="BA8442E6B87FF32023F8D53234E5E8BC" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="115">N</emphasis>
= 1); moderately stout, 2.5 times longer than wide; body shining, declivity opalescent, brown in color; eye deeply emarginated, almost completely divided; antennal club with first segment smaller than second (type 4; 
<bibRefCitation id="D48A24CAE8035CCA46311B8A640991AA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.2007.00386.x" author="Hulcr, J" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="15" pageNumber="124" refId="B16" refString="Hulcr, J, Dole, SA, Beaver, RA, Cognato, AI, 2007. . https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.2007.00386.x" url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.2007.00386.x" year="2007">Hulcr et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
); pronotum from dorsal view round (type 1; 
<bibRefCitation id="B68A5D804824DFD28EFF9421DC67CFE8" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.2007.00386.x" author="Hulcr, J" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="15" pageNumber="124" refId="B16" refString="Hulcr, J, Dole, SA, Beaver, RA, Cognato, AI, 2007. . https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.2007.00386.x" url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.2007.00386.x" year="2007">Hulcr et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), from lateral view tall (type 2; 
<bibRefCitation id="D184BB57D587E3122AF48E37AF86F278" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.2007.00386.x" author="Hulcr, J" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="15" pageNumber="124" refId="B16" refString="Hulcr, J, Dole, SA, Beaver, RA, Cognato, AI, 2007. . https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.2007.00386.x" url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1365-3113.2007.00386.x" year="2007">Hulcr et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
), anterior margin round, armed with 6 small asperities, anterior portion of pronotum densely asperate, base shagreened; elytra 1.24 times longer than pronotum, lateral sides subparallel, widest at declivital summit, disc shining, striae minutely punctate, interstriae four times broader than striae, broadest at declivital summit, declivital margin unarmed, declivity smooth,opalescent, strial punctures large, irregularly spaced.
</paragraph>
